    "actions_taken": [
      "WLE advised the Lessee of the incident",
      "WLE received crew change three days later",
      "WLE entered hospital ten days after incident for left arm treatment",
      "Company physician examination performed",
      "MRI recommended by company physician"
    ],
    "summary": "On April 6, 2015 at 0630 hours, a Wire Line Employee (WLE) nearly fell into an open hole on Platform C while walking up a stairway. The hole, measuring 25\" wide, 17\" long and 17\" deep, was left uncovered and unbarricaded after a crane mechanic removed a hatch to access a pad eye for a pull test. The WLE grabbed the handrails to prevent falling and later claimed injury to his left arm from this action. Ten days after the incident, the WLE sought hospital treatment for left arm discomfort, though a company physician found no injuries upon examination.",
